        <h3 id="intern"><a id="intern">Intern</a></h3>
<p>I am now looking for motivated (remote) summer intern students and Research Assistant (RA) for Summer. If you are interested in and want to collaborate with me, feel free to contact me with your CV. For the previous successful cases, please refer to <a href="/mentoring.html#ra">Mentoring</a>. On the other hand, before contacting me, please carefully evaluate your motivation and your time. Most students would give up in one or two weeks for various reasons (courses, English tests, job hunting, etc.). 
In that case, it would waste your time and hurt your credit in the long term. Giving up is terrible for personal development and destroys your confidence. 
One of the reasons that I did not change my major when I was a first-year student in USTC is that I thought it’s harmful to my personal development (mentally) if I gave up because of fear or uncertainty. Doing nothing is better than giving up later on.
<br />
Please check this video to know the process of applying for the research opportunity:
<a href="https://www.bilibili.com/video/BV1ut4y1M7TA/">What will happen and how I would reply if you send me an email asking the Ph.D. application and research opportunity (in Chinese)</a>. <br /></p>

<h3 id="phdmphil-students"><a id="PhD">PhD/Mphil students</a></h3>
<p>I am looking for motivated PhD/Mphil students, working on machine learning and healthcare. I have a number of quotas each year. If you are interested, feel free to drop me an email with your CV. You are also encouraged to apply through our  <a href="https://www.cse.cuhk.edu.hk/en/education/prospective-students/postgraduate-admissions-programmes/mphil-phd-programme">official website</a>, either <a href="https://www.gs.cuhk.edu.hk/admissions/programme/engineering#mphil-phd-in-computer-science-and-engineering">regular apply </a> or <a href="https://www.gs.cuhk.edu.hk/admissions/scholarships-fees/hkpfs">HKPFS</a>. You can know more about what the supervisor can provide <a href="/supervision.html">here</a>. <br /></p>

<p>With the below videos you can know more about Ph.D. study and Ph.D. applications in our group. <br />
<a href="https://www.bilibili.com/video/BV13P4y1m77s/">Students with non-CS majors are very welcomed (in Chinese)</a>.<br />
<a href="https://www.bilibili.com/video/BV1ut4y1M7TA/">What will happen and how I would reply if you send me an email asking the Ph.D. application and research opportunity (in Chinese)</a>. Most students will do a intern before receiving the offer to know whether we fit each other. <br />
[<a href="https://www.bilibili.com/video/BV1H34y1m7xV/">虚假的套瓷VS真正的套瓷</a>] <br />
[<a href="https://www.bilibili.com/video/BV1UEKdzuEZ5/">本组PhD学生招收流程及核心问题解答-2025 (in Chinese)</a>]
<br /></p>

